  "prompt": "What are some sentence examples using \"though\"?",
  "response": "Sure! Here are some sentence examples using \"though\":\n\n1. **Concessive Use:**  \n   - \"I really enjoyed the movie, though it was a bit long.\"\n   \n2. **Contrast Use:**  \n   - \"She loves hiking in the mountains, though she prefers the beach during summer.\"\n\n3. **Interjection:**  \n   - \"I didn't like the dinner; it was too salty, though.\"\n\n4. **Informal Use:**  \n   - \"I\u2019ll see you at the party, though I might be late.\"\n\n5. **Ending a Sentence:**  \n   - \"I didn\u2019t think I\u2019d come, but I will, though.\"\n\nThese examples demonstrate various ways \"though\" can be integrated into sentences to indicate contrast or concession.",
